article.headline: Wagner 64, Quinnipiac 60
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. (AP) -- Freshman forward Jamal Smith scored 18 points Saturday to lead Wagner to a 64-60 Northeast Conference win over Quinnipiac. The Seahawks trailed 36-22 at the half, but Smith's conventional three-point play with 2:11 left put them ahead for good. Senior guard DeEarnest McLemore added 11 points and junior center Durell Vinson had 10 as Wagner (11-13, 4-11) snapped a seven-game losing streak. The Seahawks had 20 offensive rebounds, 13 in the second half. Junior guard Adam Gonzalez had 14 points for Quinnipiac (11-13, 6-9). Senior guard Craig Benson and junior guard John Winchester each added 10. Trailing 62-60, Benson missed a 3-pointer from the right side with 8 seconds left. He and teammate Chris Wehye both attempted to foul Mark Porter, who came down with the rebound. But Porter was able to find Smith all alone for a lay-up with 1 second left. Wagner used a 17-4 run, culminated by a 3-pointer from Matt Vitale to take its first lead 48-45 with 8:54 left. The Seahawks missed 12 of their first 13 shots in the game and shot just 19.2 percent for the half.
